fields.html_description:
Jupiter is the East Bay's most popular beerhouse, locally owned & operated, serving its own handcrafted beers & ales along with "award-winning" wood-fired pizzas. Housed in an old livery stable from the 1890's, Jupiter exudes a European atmosphere found in the heart of Berkeley, California. (The design was inspired by the oldest bar in Berlin.)

Monday - Thursday 11:30 am - 1 am Friday 11:30 am - 1:30 am Saturday 12:00 pm - 1:30 am Sunday 1 pm - Midnight.

fields.html_description: Traditional greek salad: romaine lettuce, feta cheese, tomatoes, cucumbers, red onions, olives, pepperoncinis, and vinaigrette.
fields.description: Traditional greek salad: romaine lettuce, feta cheese, tomatoes, cucumbers, red onions, olives, pepperoncinis, and vinaigrette.

fields.html_note:
I'm pretty sure I've enjoyed this salad before, but this time it wasn't that great. I wonder if it was bad in the past, but I just never remember that 'cause I didn't have rbu to remind me before. I think I'll try it one more time and if I don't like it again I'll probably stop getting it.

The lettuce was fresh, in fact all the ingredients seemed fresh there was just some odd flavor. I liked that the feta cheese was moist and creamy, but something tells me that's probably not the way it's supposed to be and it had an odd plasticy flavor. The dressing had almost no flavor at all and was very oily. I love pepperoncinis, but I'm also very picky about them. These were spicy, but didn't have much flavor. I also love LOVE olives and these were just plain bad. They had a very bitter flavor that I never want to taste again. Needless to say, I was disappointed.

fields.html_note: Soon after writing the above review I received an email from someone at Soho Cafe explaining that they had just recently switched vendors for their feta and olives. Apparently, they weren't very happy with the product either. This is good news! Next time I'm in the neighborhood I'll try this salad again and see if the subsequent change was an improvement.
